The existence of a server is simpler in terms of management of dynamic peers in comparison to pure  peerto-peer approaches where a flood of messages to discover who is still active in the system should be used by each peer that needs to make a decision.
When the client-server service starts to perform poorly or a request for a data item comes from a client with a poor connection to the server , APPOINT can start appointing appropriate active clients of the system to serve on behalf of the server , i.e. , clients who have already volunteered their services 